name: African Waist Beads
description:
Waist beads are worn by women in many parts of Africa.  There are many different meanings for waist beads depending on the region of Africa.  Many beads are mainly worn as body ornaments or jewelries to adorn a woman's curve and shapes to attract the opposite sex or for religious purposes.  African waist beads can also be use as a guide to keep one's waistline in check, whether one is gaining or losing weight.  Whatever purpose one wears it for, it is beautiful, exoctic and it will effortlessly grace your waistline.

Note: Order comes with 3 strands of beads in the colors requested, Please let  us know on our "Contact Page" for color specifications and to be on our email list.
